(The sea-side stone.) (My folks used to tell me a bedtime story about it, way back...) (... that it was used as a sword against a big dragon.) (Nowadays, I have my doubts about that story's veracity.)
(La apudmara tono!) (Mi memoras, ke la gepatroj rakontis al mi pri i...) (... ke anta jarcentoj, i estis akra glavo kontra granda drako.)
(These doors are VERY locked.) (Literally. I think they used padlocks on padlocks..?)
(La pordoj estas EGE lositaj.) (Aspektas kvaza oni e slois sloilojn per aliaj losiloj..?)
(A window!) (It's in surprisingly good shape, given how long this place's been around.)
(Fenestro!) (Iom mirindas ke ankora ne rompiis, dum la pasintaj jardekoj.)
(Al i tiu fenesto tute mankas vitro!) (Mi kredeble povus grimpi tien, fakte...) (... sed u vere farindas?)
(This window's got no pane at all!) (I could probably fit my way in there, actually...) (... but should I?)

(Oh hey, a plaque:) ETTESBURG - HISTORICAL SITE Glue factory founded by Mr. Sal Ad in 1963. Built into the cliffside, this factory was the beating heart of Ettesburg for decades. At its peak, Sal and his factory employed an impressive 87% of the city. But in 1985, it was a victim of the largest protest in our city's history, after several workers absentmindedly followed horses into the adhesivizing machines. Fearing that the glue-workers would unionize, Ad and his family completely remodeled the factory's interior. The remodel's goal was to, with tight corridors and small rooms, hinder communication between the glue-workers. In this, the Ads succeeded - the factory's employees never did unionize, and the protests eventually pittered out. But the remodelling had some unexpected side-effects. It became so difficult to work and move product from within the factory, that despite significant effort the adhesivizer was hardly used. During the following months only 124 liters of Sal-brand glue was sold. Due to consequent financial troubles, the factory closed its doors later that year. The Ad family has since withdrawn from public life, instead living out their lives in their luxurious subterranean estate.

(Ho, jen signo:) ETBURGO - HISTORIE GRAVA LOKO Glua fabrikejo fondita de Sal ATO je 1963. Parte konstruita ene de kavernsistemo, i tiu fabrikejo longe estis la koro de la Etburga ekonomio dum jaroj. Je la plej alta pinto, Sal kaj sia fabrikejo dungis 87% da Etburganoj. Sed je 1985, i estis viktimo de la plej vigla protesto en nia historio, post kelkaj laborantoj neintence kondukiis al la gluigmaino anstata evaloj. Timante ke la dungitoj unuius al sindikato, ATO kun siaj parencoj entute rekonstruis la internon de la fabrikejo. La celo estis, per mallaraj koridoroj kaj ambroj, malfaciligi komunikadon inter la gluistoj. Je tio, la Atoj sukcesis - la gluistoj ne fodnis sindikaton, kaj la maltranvkilo fine elerpiis. Sed la nova arano anka venigis aliajn problemojn. Tiom malfacilis labori kaj movi produktojn en la fabrikejo, ke malgra multa peno, neniu sukcesis logi evalojn al la gluigmaino. Dum la sekvontaj monatoj sole vendiis 123 litroj da Sal-marka gluo. Pro monproblemoj, tiujare fermiis la fabrikejo. Ekde tiu tago, la familio Ato enfermiis en si mem, kaante sin en sia luksa domego subtera.

(Ho, jen signo:) !! ENIRU NEPRE NE !! DANERA LOKO - VENENA MATERIO (P, kredeble troigas.)
(Dayum, that's one big tree!) (... not sure why I'm acting surprised. It's been there for decades, now.)
(Fek', kia turgranda arbo!) (... mi ne scias, kial mi miras. i jam estis tie dum jardekoj.)
(The local Kopimi church.) (I don't wanna judge anyone's religious beliefs, but...) (... the doors are locked, and I can hear screaming from the inside.)
(La loka preejo Kopimin-a.) (Mi malemas jui la religiajn kredojn de aliuloj, sed...) (... la pordoj estas lositaj, kaj adeblas kriado lata post i.)
(I'm pretty sure this is a side-entrance to the upper-story apartments.) (I'm not a tenant, so... I'll stick around down here.)
(Kredeble estas eniro al la supraj apartamentoj.) (... mi ne loas tie, do mi restos tie i.)
(The teahouse!) (I'm not in the mood, but maybe later.)
(La teejo!) (Mi ne soifas uste nun, sed eble poste.)
(The Ettesburg Journal's office!) (Man, it'd be cool to be a source for some expose.) (Maybe someday!)
(La oficejo de la Etburga Folio!) (Mi revas iutage intervjuii pro grava esploro...)
(The grocery.) (It's named after a "Mina," but the grocer's name is "Bret"...) (How're the two related? Heck if I know!)
(La iutagaa vendejo.) (i nomias "MINA" sed la prizorganto nomias "BRET"?) (Kiel ili rilatas estas mistero neesplorinda.)
(Sasha's staying here, I think?)
(Saa nun loas tie i, mi kredas..?)

(Through the window monkeys can be seen feverishly typing on computers.) (... Wait. Monkeys?!) (Oh, right.) (The journal's trying out an experiment on how many monkeys it takes to write an article.) (At least one, I'd reckon.)
(Tra la fenestro videblas fervore verkantaj... simioj?!) (Ho, jes.) (La urnalo free starigis eksperimenton: "Kiom da simioj oni bezonas sukcese skribi artikolon?") (Almena unu, mi konjektas.)
(Through the window people can be seen sipping from teacups at a relaxed pace.) (It looks so warm and welcoming, as per usual!)
(Tra la fenestro videblas kelkaj homoj ripoze trinketantaj el teotasoj.) (Kia varma, bonvena etoso.)

(I might be colorblind, but even I can tell that the florist's mural is eye-popping in its use of color.) (In the window there are two skillfuly-made bouquets posed so strikingly that they should catch any decent person's attention.) (What a beautiful place!)

(E kolorblindulo kiel mi povas tuj rimarki la okulfrapajn kolorojn de la belfarita murpentrao.) (Preter la fenestro estas du artfaritaj floraroj metitaj tiom atente ke e la plej senespera laiku in atus.) (Kia sankta loko!)
(Blocks of fine cheese on tempt those who pass the grocer's window sill.) (... wait, won't those go bad?)
(Fromao altkvalita sur la fenestrobreto tentas preterpasantojn de la iovendejeto.) (... Momenton. u ne la fromao putrios tie?!)
(Pop's workshop.) (He used to have me help him in his work, as a kid.) (God, that was boring!)
(La laborejo de pajo.) (Mi memoras ke, dum infanao, li ofte petis min helpi lin tie.) (Fek', tiom enuigis!!)
(The florist!) (What a beautiful place!) (By God, I'd take anything life throws at me with ease if I could work here.)
(La florvendejo!) (Lakutime, i odoras loge kaj anelece.) (Je Dio, mi plene kontentus je vivo laborante tie i!)
(The library. I bet my mother's hard at work right now, moving books here and there...) (Or whatever the heck librarians do.) (I'd rather not go in. Boredom is such a boring way to die.)

(La biblioteko. La patrino kredeble fervore laboras uste nun, movante librojn de tie al tie...) (... a kion ajn faras bibliotekistoj.) (Mi preferus ne eniri. Profunda enuo estas profunde enua mortigo.)
(Home sweet home.) (It's bigger on the inside than it is on the outside, trust me.)
(Nia kara hejmo.) (i aspektas pligranda deinterne, mi uras!)
(Ficus retusa, often used in bonsai. Good for beginners.) (I've only ever trained it into shrub-form, though.) (When I was younger, I liked to hide things from my parents in this Ficus.)
(Fikuso retuso, ofte uzata kiel bonsaja planto. Facilas al komencantoj.) (Mi simple tondas in al dika herbao, tamen.) (Anta iuj jaroj, mi kutimis kai aferojn de la gepatroj en tiu i Fikuso, mdr.)
(It looks like there's a crack here...) (I think I can shimmy through.)
(Aspektas kvaza estas fendeto en la muro?) (Mi kredeble povus preteriri in...)
